## Story

### 1. קוֹלוֹת מִלְמָעְלָה (Voices From Above)
![Four children with animal features look up as a shining cloud appears above them.](section001.png)
וַיְהִי קוֹל גָּדוֹל מִלְמַעְלָה בַּבָּיִת. הַיְלָדִים שׁוֹמְעִים קוֹל. הַקּוֹל מְדַבֵּר.

---

### 2. וַיֹּאמֶר הַקּוֹל (And the Voice Said)
![A bright word bubble from above says something while kids listen.](section002.png)
וַיֹּאמֶר הַקּוֹל: "לֵכוּ אֶל בֵּיבִּי דַּרְת' וֵיידֶר וְסִלְחוּ לוֹ!"

---

### 3. מַה זֶּה? (What Is This?)
![Kids look at each other, confused, some with paws over their mouths.](section003.png)
אָמְרוּ הַיְלָדִים: "מַה זֶּה? לָמָּה לֵלֶכֶת אֵלָיו?"

---

### 4. וַיֵּלְכוּ הַיְלָדִים לְפִנָּה (And the Children Go to a Corner)
![Kids huddle together in a quiet corner, whispering.](section004.png)
הַיְלָדִים הָלְכוּ יַחַד לְפִנָּה. הֵם לָחֲשׁוּ.

---

### 5. וַיֹּאמְרוּ: "רַע הוּא!" (“And They Said: ‘He Is Evil!’”)
![Children look upset, one shakes a finger, others whisper.](section005.png)
וַיֹּאמְרוּ: "רַע הוּא! אֵיךְ נִסְלַח לוֹ?"

---

### 6. "לָמָּה נִסְלַח?" (“Why Should We Forgive?”)
![Aaron as dinosaur, Aurelia as panda, Evan as owl, Isaac as koala—each asks “why?”](section006.png)
אָמַר אַהֲרֹן: "לָמָּה נִסְלַח?" אָמְרָה אוֹרֵלְיָה: "רַע לוֹ".

---

### 7. קוֹל מִלְמָעְלָה שׁוּב (Voice From Above Again)
![The glowing top of the room shines once more, voice calls down.](section007.png)
וַיְהִי קוֹל עוֹד: "סִלְחוּ לוֹ! אֲנִי אָמַרְתִּי."

---

### 8. וַיְלַחֲשׁוּ יַחַד (And They Whisper Together)
![Children huddle, ears pressed close, eyes wide.](section008.png)
הַיְלָדִים לָחֲשׁוּ יַחַד: "אֵיךְ נַעֲשֶׂה?"

---

### 9. אֲבָל יֵשׁ קֶשֶׁה (But There Is Difficulty)
![Isaac frowns; Evan shrugs; Aurelia shakes head; Aaron pulls face.](section009.png)
אָמַר יִצְחָק: "קוֹשֶׁה לִסְלֹחַ." וְאֵבֶן אָמַר: "קָשֶׁה לָנוּ."

---

### 10. "נִסְלַח אוֹ לֹא?" (“Forgive or Not?”)
![Speech bubbles show “Yes” and “No” floating.](section010.png)
אוֹרֵלְיָה אָמְרָה: "נִסְלַח?" אַהֲרֹן אָמַר: "אוּלַי לֹא."

---

### 11. קוֹל: "אֲהַבְתִּי כֻּלָּם" (Voice: “I Loved All”)
![The voice thunders: “I loved everyone!”](section011.png)
קָרָא הַקּוֹל: "אָהַבְתִּי כֻּלָּם, טוֹבִים וְרָעִים."

---

### 12. הַיְלָדִים מַבִּיטִים לְמַעְלָה (Children Look Up)
![Children gaze up, thoughtful, mouths closed, animal-ears pricked.](section012.png)
הַיְלָדִים מַבִּיטִים לְמַעְלָה וְשׁוֹקְלִים.

---

### 13. "יוֹדֵעַ אֲדֹנָי" (“The Lord Knows”)
![Evan, now more serious, nods to the sky.](section013.png)
אָמַר אֵבֶן: "יוֹדֵעַ אֲדֹנָי אֶת דְּרָכֵּנוּ."

---

### 14. שׁוֹאֲלִים מַדּוּעַ (They Ask “Why”)
![A big “Why?” hangs above the kids, who look perplexed.](section014.png)
שׁוֹאֲלִים כֻּלָּם: "מַדּוּעַ סְלִיחָה לְרָע?"

---

### 15. קוֹל: "אֵהַב וְסָלַח" (“Voice: ‘Love and Forgive’”)
![Hearts and halos appear in a word-bubble from above.](section015.png)
קָרָא הַקּוֹל: "אֵהַב וְסָלַח, כִּי זֶה דָּבָר טוֹב."

---

### 16. קוֹל וְקָשֶה (The Voice and the Difficulty)
![Children scratch heads, some smile, others still frown.](section016.png)
הקּוֹל מְדַבֵּר. קָשֶׁה לִסְלֹחַ. טוֹב לְהַאֲזִין.

---

### 17. אוֹר בַּבַּיִת (Light in the House)
![Suddenly the house is full of new, bright light, and the children smile a little.](section017.png)
אוֹר גָּדול בַּבַּיִת. הַיְלָדִים מַבָּטִים זֶה אֶל זֶה.

---

### 18. וַיֹּאמְרוּ יַחַד (And They Said Together)
![Children, animal-features still on, nod and decide to do it.](section018.png)
וַיֹּאמְרוּ יַחַד: "נֵלֵךְ. נֶסְלַח."

---

### 19. סוֹף הַקּוֹל (The Voice Ends)
![The shining above dims. Children look ready for the next adventure.](section019.png)
הַקּוֹל שָׁקַט. עַכְשָׁו יֵשׁ שַׁלְוָה.

---

### 20. יַחַד לַדֶּרֶךְ (Together on the Way)
![Kids begin to move forward, together, animal shapes blending.](section020.png)
הַיְלָדִים יַחַד. יָצְאוּ לַדֶּרֶךְ לְסְלֹחַ. יַחַד!

---

## Vocabulary

### Nouns

| Hebrew (with niqqud) | English Gloss         |
|----------------------|----------------------|
| קוֹל                 | voice                |
| מִלְמַעְלָה          | from above           |
| פִּנָּה               | corner               |
| קֹשֶׁה               | difficulty           |
| דֶּרֶךְ              | way, path            |
| אוֹר                 | light                |
| שַׁלְוָה              | peace, calm          |

### Verbs

| Hebrew (with niqqud)     | English Gloss                 |
|--------------------------|------------------------------|
| שָׁמַע                   | to hear                      |
| אָמַר                   | to say                       |
| לָחַשׁ                   | to whisper                   |
| סָלַח                   | to forgive                   |
| יָכֹל                   | to be able                   |
| יָצָא                   | to go out                    |
| אָהַב                   | to love                      |
| מַבִּיט                  | to look, gaze                |
| שׁוֹאֵל                  | to ask                       |
| שָׁקַט                   | to be quiet                  |
| הִבִּין                  | to understand                |

### Adjectives / Adverbs

| Hebrew (with niqqud) | English Gloss         |
|----------------------|----------------------|
| גָּדוֹל               | great, big (here “great/loud”) |
| טוֹב                  | good                  |
| רַע                   | evil                  |
| קָשֶׁה                | difficult             |
| יַחַד                 | together              |

### Pronominal / Particles

| Hebrew (with niqqud) | English Gloss           |
|----------------------|------------------------|
| אֶל                  | to, toward             |
| עֲלֵי                | upon (archaizing for B-Hebrew flavor) |
| לָמָּה                | why                    |
| מַה                  | what                   |
| אוּלַי                | perhaps                |
| מִדּוּעַ              | why, why so            |
| כִּי                  | because, for           |
| עַכְשָׁו              | now                    |
| זֶה                  | this                   |

---

## Grammar

- Quoted speech using וַיֹּאמֶר… (“And he said…”, “And she said…”)
- Infinitive construct: "לֵלֶכֶת" (“to go”), "לִסְלֹחַ" (“to forgive”)
- Simple “why” and “how” questions: "לָמָּה…?", "מַדּוּעַ…?"
- Repetition of perfect verb forms for direct narration (וַיֹּאמֶר, אָמַר, אָמְרוּ)
- Simple expression of opposites: "טוֹב" / "רַע"; contextually re-used
- Vocabulary of feelings, especially forgiveness, difficulty, love, and peace
- Use of conjunction “וְ” ("and") for sequencing and unity
- Continued use of collective subject ("children together": "יַחַד")
- Minimal introduction of new verb forms—infinitive and dialogue only

---

*End of Chapter 5*
